
[1]weariness

   WEARINESS, n. [from weary.]

   1. The state of being weary or tired; that lassitude or exhaustion of
   strength which is induced by labor; fatigue.

   With weariness and wine oppresd.

   2. Lassitude; uneasiness proceeding from continued waiting,
   disappointed expectation or exhausted patience, or from other cause.
